         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511"><!-- p2l6-r15 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Hd1e108">Rubrica 15</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De vulgari seu famosa asseueratione facti</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>
      ¶ De vulgari seu famosa 
      <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>asseueratione. Rubrica. 15
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/><ref>ISocrates in exhorta
      <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>tionibus. c. 2.</ref>
      <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e129">Uerere crimina tam etsi falsa sunt:
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>nam plerique veritatem ignorant: opi
        <lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>nionem autem coniectant.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e137">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
             ¶ <ref>Uirgilius eneid. li. 4. circa princi.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e141">Fama malum: quo non aliud velocius vllum
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>Mobilitate viget: viresque acquirit eundo.
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>Parua motu primo: mox sese attollit in auras
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Ingrediturque solo: et caput inter nubila con
        <lb ed="#V" n="69" break="no"/>dit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e156"> /
               <ref>Li. 7. ante med. et in. 3. et in. 8.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e158">Fama volat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e164">
               <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>
             ¶ <ref>Tullius topicorum. c. 4. et fi.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e168">Fama vulgi est
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>quoddam multitudinis testimonium.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e174">
               <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>
             ¶ <ref>Quintilianus declam. 17 declam. et finali</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e178">Rumor est res sine teste sine iudice res ex in
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>certis: improbissima: maligna: fallax.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e186">
               <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>
             ¶ <ref>Seneca in prouerb.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e190">Bona opinio hominum
        <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>tutior est pecunia. Bona fama in tenebris
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>proprium splendorem obtinet. Damnum appellandum
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>est cum mala fama lucrum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e200">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
             ¶ <ref>Marcialis cocus li. vndique suscepto. c. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e204">Rumor falsidicus surgit: et ecce cadit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e210">
               <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>
             ¶ <ref>Auctor libro de formula honeste vite. c. 4</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e214">Rumoribus criminum et suspitionibus mini
        <lb ed="#V" n="84" break="no"/>me sis credulus: sed potius malignis qui per
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>speciem simplicitatis ad nocendum aliquibus
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>surrepunt oppositissimus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e227">
               <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>
             ¶ <ref>Lucanus li. i.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e231">Innumeras soluit falsa pre
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>conia linguas.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e237">
               <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>
             ¶ <ref>Boetius de consolatione lib. i. c. 12. et pen.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e241">Plures magnum nomen falsis vulgi opinioni <!--144.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="59-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1" break="no"/>bus abstulerunt.
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>Sapiens bonum suum non popularim rumore:
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>sed conscientie veritate metitur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e260">
               <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>
             ¶ <ref>Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 7. e. 2.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e264">Nulla
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>potestas est que qualitatem fame sue de ore
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>hominum possit auferre.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e272">
               <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>
             ¶ <ref>Auctor rudium dogmatis li. 2</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e276">Error minimo
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>crescit: sed non cito fama quiescit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>Quamuis mentitur crescit eundo tamen.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e284">
               <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>
             ¶ <ref>Prouerb. metri. extraordi. li. vag.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e288">Fama bo
        <lb ed="#V" n="11" break="no"/>ni lente: volat inuidia retinente.
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>Fama repleta malis: auium deducitur alis.</quote>
            </p>
